# shadcn/ui (Required)

If shadcn has a component for the job, **always use it** — never build a custom substitute.

1. Check `src/components/ui/` first.
2. If missing: find it at [ui.shadcn.com](https://ui.shadcn.com) and install:
   `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`
3. Import from `@/components/ui/<name>`.
4. Style: `radix-nova` (see `components.json`). Icons: `lucide-react`.

# Typography (Required)

**Never** use raw `<h1>`–`<h6>`, `<p>`, or ad-hoc text classes for visible text.

Always use `Typography` from `@/components/common/Typography`:

```tsx
import { Typography } from "@/components/common/Typography";

<Typography variant="h2">Title</Typography>
<Typography variant="body" color="muted">Description</Typography>
```

Variants: `display`, `h1`–`h6`, `section-title`, `body`, `body-sm`, `caption`, `label`, etc. Use `as` only when semantics require a different element.
